
FEB. 18, 2018

Sara Naggar Bourne and Matthew Aaron Kaplan are to be married Feb. 18 at the Ritz-Carlton in San Francisco. Rabbi Michal Bourne, the bride’s aunt, is to officiate.
The bride, 33, is of counsel at Genentech, a biotechnology company in San Francisco. She graduated from Stanford and received a law degree from Emory University.
She is the daughter of Dr. Jeffrey A. Bourne of West New York, N.J., and the late Michaela N. Bourne, who lived in Short Hills, N.J. The bride’s father is a pediatrician in private practice in West New York. Her mother worked in San Francisco for the Bureau of Jewish Education, a Jewish nonprofit now called Jewish LearningWork.
The groom, also 33, is on the public policy team at Lyft, the transportation company in San Francisco. Previously, Mr. Kaplan served as the national surrogate finance director for Hillary Clinton’s 2016 presidential campaign. He graduated from Oberlin College in Ohio.
He is the son of Jana E. Kaplan of Pomona, Calif., and the late Kenneth J. Kaplan, who lived in Claremont, Calif. The groom’s father worked in sales for Georgia Boot, a shoe company with headquarters in Franklin, Tenn.
The couple met in 2015 and had their first date at Sonoma Restaurant & Wine Bar in Washington.
